bio.experienceSummary: Hi! My name is Sarah, and I'm 25 years old, based in Union NJ. I graduated from Montclair State University in 2021 and have seven years of childcare experience, including working at daycares and through Care. com. While working at the YMCA, I also obtained my CPR certification. I'm excited to learn more about your little ones and hope to hear from you soon!

Hello! I'm Kerene, a dedicated nanny with over 5 years of experience in childcare and a passion for nurturing young minds. I began my professional journey in 2014, outside of caring for my younger siblings since they were babies, and now they are aged 8, 10, and 13. Alongside my role as a teacher assistant, I've honed my skills in organizing activities, preparing meals, bedtime stories, and even teaching a bit of French. Creating a safe, structured, and loving environment where children can thrive brings me immense joy. I look forward to bringing my experience, positivity, and genuine care to your family!

description.displayText: This review is long overdue! From our first phone call, I knew Kerene was the one. Not only is she punctual, dependable and responsible, but she is so very loving and attentive to our 2 young children. She became family from day 1. My children loved all the fun adventures they went on and always came home with a story. Never a dull moment. I knew my children were in the best care and never had to worry leaving them. She also helped keep the home neat and prepared meals when needed. Kerene is an absolute God sent!

bio.experienceSummary: I have over 20 years of experience working with infants and children! I have a great passion for working with, and caring for them! They play a major part in my life! I have four children, which includes twins, and five grandhildren. Most of my free time is spent with them

description.originalText: I am a FTM. Kathy helped guide me on how to take care of my 4 month old while also caring for him during the summer. She is kind, caring, and knows her stuff! She's knowledgeable and flexible. I enjoyed having Kathy care for my son. I would hire her if I needed child care again.

bio.experienceSummary: While in high school I had the pleasure of working at a non profit after school center tutoring, leading dance, and reading classes. During my time there I was promoted to a team leader where I was in charge of managing other teens. I had the opportunity to go on many professional visits and receive extensive one-on-one coaching and support from the directors and coordinators of the center. After graduating high school I began college and working at a charter school in Jersey City where I became an assistant teacher for 1st and 2nd grade. I also had the opportunity to babysit my former high school math teachers children after school hours and on weekends. Last May I was blessed with my baby girl, being a first time mother has been nothing but great. I have many years of experience with children. I am very patient, loving and reliable. Teaching and being around children is a passion of mine and I look forward to all the nanny opportunities that I will have.

I'm passionate about fostering children's growth and development, and as a childcare provider with a year of experience, Im going to provide a nurturing and stimulating environment for your child. My patient, calm, and friendly nature creates a safe and welcoming atmosphere.

I believe in open and transparent communication with parents and follow their preferred method to discuss their child's day or any concerns. I am very comfortable enforcing household rules to ensure a structured and consistent environment.

My approach to childcare includes a variety of age-appropriate games and activities, such as outdoor sports, board games, and educational games that promote learning. I have an associate degree on education and am a certified teacher, which enhances my ability to provide a well-rounded and enriching experience for your child.

I am available to care for one or more child . I also speak English, Spanish, Portuguese, pet friendly and a good cooker .

Hi ! My name is De'mia , I am a 2nd year psychology major attending Rowan uni. I have been caring for children for 5 1/2 years now & extremely experienced ( all ages ) & willing to help out with any needs they may have ! I love working with children & watching their little mind expand & develop through the years of care. I also am very experienced with special needs munchkins ( autistic kids, Sorrell palsy syndrome , speech delay , severe cases of ADHD) I am very well educated with the communication /education of children in all ages , (esp infants) I look forward to introducing them into new ways of expressing themselves, communicating, understanding & mindfulness . Help around the house , tidying up , meal prep & open to assistance with potty training, sign language, studying , reading , writing, time management, pick up /drop off & getting child on schedule and any extracurricular activities that can be discussed , also ! I do have a resume that also can be sent over for reference.

As a dedicated mother of two young children and a professional with over 12 years of experience in early childhood education, I am passionate about nurturing and guiding young minds. I hold a master's degree in Early Childhood Education and have had the privilege of working in various roles including preschool teacher, assistant director, and school education manager. Originally from New York, I bring a wealth of knowledge, compassion, and expertise to every caregiving experience, ensuring that each child under my care feels supported, safe, and inspired to learn and grow.

Hello!

I'd describe my personality as caring, fun and somewhat adventurous.

I like working with kids because I like the innocence of how they talk, think and express themselves. I love their truthfulness.

I believe time, benefits and even pay rate are negotiable as long as both parties try to be fair.

I started working with kids when I was 17, I used to teach back in Brazil, then came to the US as an Au Pair. I've been a nanny, babysitter, mother's help and I currently have a 8yo boy (who WON'T depend on me during working hours). I currently work for a family and I'm looking for a second job.

In my spare time, I like to play tennis and enjoy my family.

My skills include being understanding, following directions and being pro active.
I have knowledge in gentle parenting and ADHD resources and tools. 

I believe in respecting children, leading by example and guiding them through difficult times. I also believe in limits and manners.

description.originalText:
We had the pleasure of having Lannes care for our baby girl, and she truly excelled in developing our child's skills and providing a nurturing environment. Her approach to early development was fantastic, and we noticed significant progress during her 10 months with us.

Additionally, Lannes was helpful with light housekeeping, keeping our space tidy and organized, which was a great relief for us as new parents.

We appreciate the time she spent with our family.

bio.experienceSummary: I have years of experience caring for children of all ages, from infants to preteens. I am committed to providing a safe, fun, and nurturing environment for the children in my care. I truly enjoy engaging with little ones; I find it rewarding to foster connections with them and be apart of their development. I was a volunteer teacher and babysitter ranging from 2 years old to 12 years old at church for four years. Besides this experience, I was also a caregiver for children of elementary ages, infants, and toddlers for two years. I am also a fluent speaker of Portuguese. I would love to speak with you personally about your family's needs. Please feel free to contact me. Thank you!
